515 – 16 . Carmichael MS . An eilean Beag iosal / eadar Nial s Siol Ailean ;
K . C . C . A chuir iad ann an criochaibh / Eadar Niall is Sìol Ailein ; Òranaiche Ann an eilein ìosal / Eadar Niall is Ailein .
The Òranaiche version is adopted here , because it is known that Dòmhnall mac Iain ’ ic Sheumais was living on Eriskay , which is between Barra , belonging to the MacNeils , and South Uist , belonging to the MacDonalds of Clanranald , the patronymic of whose chief was Mac ’ ic Ailein .

579 – 627 . Canon MacLean , Ann an làth ’ rach an Tighearna ;
T underlined as if to question ; K . C . C . , Ann an làrach an Tighearna .
Cf . Dinneen , láithreach , ‘ presence ’ . The presence of their laird or chief appears to be indicated , in his judicial capacity .

