678 . For Ciorcabost read Circeabost ;
but Dr . A . MacLean tells me that he once heard Calum Johnston sing this line as Eadar Circeadal is Ruadal .
This makes better sense , as these places exist in South Uist , on the south side of Loch Eynort and the south side of Loch Skipport respectively .
